import java.util.Stack;

public class ParenthesesCounter {
    public static int countValidParentheses(String input) {
        Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<>();
        int validCount = 0;

        for (char ch : input.toCharArray()) {
            if (ch == '(') {
                stack.push(ch);
            } else if (ch == ')') {
                if (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() == '(') {
                    stack.pop();
                    validCount++;
                } else {
                    // Invalid case: unmatched closing parenthesis
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        return validCount;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "((()))()";
        int validParentheses = countValidParentheses(input);
        System.out.println("Number of valid parentheses: " + validParentheses);
    }
}
```

This code will count the number of valid parentheses pairs in a given string. It uses a `Stack` to match each opening parenthesis with a corresponding closing one. If it finds a mismatch or an unmatched closing parenthesis, it stops counting and returns the current valid count.

